  "time_ut": 1660110273,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db8\u0dca\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dca\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d87\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca \u0d86\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dae\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba \u0db1\u0d82\u0dc0\u0db8\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Let's come to consensus from disagreement and boost the economy",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Dissent does not always lead to misfortune. Disagreement is natural when representing people with different goals and aspirations. Basically, different political parties represent the goals and aspirations of different people. But dialogues between political parties should be built to clarify the common goals of political parties that have different goals and aspirations. Then common expectations and goals affecting everyone can be clearly identified and a consensus can be reached. After reaching the consensus, what should be done is to prepare the program towards those common goals and work together to overcome those goals.",
        "The new president invited all parties and groups for discussions in his policy statement at the beginning of the parliamentary session. It appeared that the invitation was mostly fruitful because political groups with different views accepted the invitation and participated in the discussions. The representatives of several main parties were heard saying that the first round of negotiations was successful.",
        "To get out of this economic crisis and not to fall into such crises in the future, it is extremely important to reach consensus among disagreements. We have many common goals to overcome as a nation. Stabilization of the economy should be done urgently. At the same time, there are other extremely important things that need to be agreed upon through discussion. It is extremely important to continue these dialogues to achieve other objectives after reaching consensus to take decisions related to the urgent need to stabilize the economy.",
        "It is clear that no political party is 100 percent satisfied with the current electoral system. However, the political parties do not like the proportional voting system among the people. When contesting elections through proportional representation at the district level, it is the candidate who has good wealth who gets the ability to run a strong campaign throughout the district. There is currently no system to limit candidates' election expenses. The member elected at the district level is not directly accountable to a constituency. Under the previous single system, the MP had to directly represent the people of his constituency. It is the opinion of the common people that they are disqualified from the district level under proportional representation. The way some MPs behave in the Parliament is a confirmation of that opinion of the general public. Because of this, it is the responsibility of the party representatives to set up an election system in which the right people's representatives are appointed to the parliament. It is extremely important to reach a consensus to build a proper electoral system through a dialogue between the parties.",
        "If the abolition of the proportional representation system alone is disadvantageous to some small parties, their views should be consulted and a compromise should be reached to work out a proper mixed system.",
        "At the same time, it is more appropriate to reach some compromises that affect the economy and agriculture industry for the future benefit of the country. By now we have learned lessons due to the ban on chemical fertilizers. In future (as in India) it would be fruitful to reach a consensus to seek the support of an expert committee with in-depth knowledge of the subject in order to take policy decisions related to agriculture. Also, decisions related to foreign investments, making decisions regarding loss-making government institutions, reaching consensus between political parties for decisions related to export economy are more useful for future work.",
        "The ultimate goal of the common struggle that brought about a strong political change in the country was to bring about a change in the system. A compromise with the ultimate goal of the struggle is as important as all compromises."
      ],
